//383. Ransom Note
//Given two strings ransomNote and magazine, return true if ransomNote can be constructed using the letters from magazine.
//Each letter in magazine can only be used once.
//Example 1:
//Input: ransomNote = "a", magazine = "b"
//Output: false
//Example 2:
//Input: ransomNote = "aa", magazine = "ab"
//Output: false
//Example 3:
//Input: ransomNote = "aa", magazine = "aab"
//Output: true


Brute Force Approach ->

Compare every character of ransomNote with magazine.
Whenever a matching unused character is found, mark it as used.
If any character cannot be matched, return false.

class Solution {
public:
    bool canConstruct(string ransomNote, string magazine) {
        vector<bool> used(magazine.size(), false);
        for(int i = 0; i < ransomNote.size(); i++) {
            bool found = false;
            for(int j = 0; j < magazine.size(); j++) {
                if(!used[j] && ransomNote[i] == magazine[j]) {
                    used[j] = true;
                    found = true;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if(!found) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
};

Intuition ->

For every character in ransomNote:

Search the magazine.

If an unused matching character exists,
mark it as used.

If no match is found,
construction is impossible.

Complexity Analysis ->

Time Complexity -> O(n × m)

where:

n = length of ransomNote

m = length of magazine

Reason:

For every character in ransomNote,
we may scan the entire magazine.

Space Complexity -> O(m)

Reason:

A boolean array stores whether each magazine character has already been used.

------------------------------------------------------------

Optimal Approach -> (Frequency Counting)

class Solution {
public:
    bool canConstruct(string ransomNote, string magazine) {

        vector<int> freq(26, 0);

        for(char c : magazine) {
            freq[c - 'a']++;
        }

        for(char c : ransomNote) {

            freq[c - 'a']--;

            if(freq[c - 'a'] < 0) {
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
};

Intuition ->

Count how many times each character appears in magazine.

Then consume characters while traversing ransomNote.

If any character's frequency becomes negative,

that character was needed more times than it existed.

So construction is impossible.

Complexity Analysis ->

Time Complexity -> O(n + m)

where:

n = length of ransomNote

m = length of magazine

Reason:

One traversal of magazine.

One traversal of ransomNote.

Space Complexity -> O(1)

Reason:

Only a frequency array of size 26 is used.

